      "id": "concept-load-balancing",
      "title": "Load Balancing",
      "description": "Load balancing distributes client requests across multiple servers to optimize resource usage, maximize throughput, and prevent any single machine from being overloaded.  For example, an application may use multiple web servers behind an L4 (network-level) or L7 (application-level) load balancer to handle large request volumes, automatically routing traffic away from failed instances. Enhanced with additional resources and perspectives.",
