    {
      "id": "concept-content-delivery-networks-cdns",
      "title": "Content Delivery Networks (CDNs)",
      "description": "A CDN is a geographically distributed network of proxy servers that caches content (like images, scripts, video) closer to end users, reducing latency and offloading origin servers.  CDNs improve load times by serving content from the nearest edge server.  For example, a static image or video asset is replicated to edge nodes around the world so users download it from a local cache, accelerating delivery. Enhanced with additional resources and perspectives.",
      "estimatedMinutes": 60,
      "difficulty": "Beginner",
      "category": "Core Fundamentals",
