    {
      "id": "concept-cap-theorem-consistency-models",
      "title": "CAP Theorem & Consistency Models",
      "description": "The CAP theorem states that in a distributed system you can guarantee only two of Consistency, Availability, and Partition Tolerance simultaneously.  In practice, systems often trade strict consistency for availability under partition (favoring eventual consistency).  For example, many NoSQL stores sacrifice C for P to remain available when nodes fail. Understanding CAP guides how we handle data replication and consistency (strong vs eventual). Enhanced with additional resources and perspectives.",
      "estimatedMinutes": 60,
      "difficulty": "Beginner",
      "category": "Core Fundamentals",
      "orderIndex": 5,
