    {
      "id": "concept-sharding-partitioning",
      "title": "Sharding (Partitioning)",
      "description": "Sharding splits large data sets horizontally across multiple database instances (shards) to scale beyond a single server's capacity.  Each shard holds a subset of the data (often by key or geography).  For instance, a user database might shard by user ID range so queries/transactions for different users go to different servers.  Sharding enables parallelism and is vital for very large datasets.",
      "estimatedMinutes": 60,
      "difficulty": "Intermediate",
      "category": "Core Fundamentals",
      "orderIndex": 7,
