    {
      "id": "concept-publishsubscribe-pubsub",
      "title": "Publish/Subscribe (Pub/Sub)",
      "description": "Pub/Sub systems (e.g. Kafka topics, Google Pub/Sub) deliver messages from publishers to all subscribed consumers.  Unlike a single-queue model, pub/sub fans out each message to multiple subscribers.  For example, a log-in event might be published to a topic so that multiple services (analytics, notification, logging) each receive it. This supports scalable event-driven and broadcast architectures.",
