    {
      "id": "concept-rate-limiting",
      "title": "Rate Limiting",
      "description": "Rate limiting throttles client requests (e.g. X requests per minute per user) to prevent abuse or overload.  Common algorithms include fixed windows, sliding logs, or token/leaky bucket algorithms, often implemented with Redis or in-network proxies. For example, an API gateway might allow only 100 calls/min from a given IP by using a token bucket in Redis to track credits.",
