    {
      "id": "concept-microservices-architecture",
      "title": "Microservices Architecture",
      "description": "Microservices break a monolith into independently deployable services, each responsible for a single business capability.  Microservices allow teams to scale, develop, and deploy services independently.  For example, Spotify runs separate services for authentication, streaming, and playlists, each with its own data store. Communication is via lightweight APIs or messaging, often orchestrated through an API gateway.",
      "estimatedMinutes": 120,
      "difficulty": "Intermediate",
