    {
      "id": "concept-security",
      "title": "Security",
      "description": "Security involves protecting data and access.  In system design, always encrypt data in transit (TLS) and at rest.  Use robust authentication/authorization (e.g. OAuth2, JWT tokens).  For example, APIs should require HTTPS, and user identities might be managed via OAuth2/OpenID Connect so services need not store passwords directly.  Also design to handle threats (rate-limit abusive requests, validate inputs).",
      "estimatedMinutes": 60,
      "difficulty": "Advanced",
      "category": "Core Fundamentals",
      "orderIndex": 16,
