    {
      "id": "concept-consensus-algorithms-paxos-raft",
      "title": "Consensus Algorithms (Paxos, Raft)",
      "description": "Consensus protocols ensure a majority of nodes agree on a value, even with failures.  Algorithms like Paxos or Raft are used for leader election and consistent replication of logs across nodes.  For example, Zookeeper uses Zab (a variant of Paxos) to manage distributed locks, and etcd uses Raft for leader election.  These guarantee consistency in systems that require a single source of truth.",
      "estimatedMinutes": 120,
      "difficulty": "Advanced",
      "category": "Core Fundamentals",
